Enum DLMatch

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<DLMatch>
public enum DLMatch
extends java.lang.Enum<DLMatch>

Enumeration of the various Description Logic based matching types for any two classes (concepts) C1, C2; or any two data ranges D1, D2.

Enum Constant Summary
DISJOINT
          C1 and C2 are disjoint, or D1 and D2 are disjoint.
EXACT
          C1 is equivalent to C2, or D1 is equivalent to D2.
FAIL
          None of EXACT, SUBSUME, PLUG_IN, DISJOINT holds for C1, C2 and D1, D2 respectively.
PLUG_IN
          C1 is a super class of C2, or D1 is a super data range of D2.
SUBSUME
          C1 is subsumed by (is a subclass of) C2, or D1 is subsumed by (is a sub data range of) D2.
